    {
      "name": "query_type_classification",
      "content": "Classify the following query into one of these types based on its semantic meaning and complexity.\n\nExamples:\nQuery: \"What is the capital of France?\"\nReasoning: Asking for a specific fact (capital city)\nType: factual\n\nQuery: \"How many people live in Tokyo?\"\nReasoning: Asking for a numerical value (population count)\nType: numerical\n\nQuery: \"Why did World War II start?\"\nReasoning: Asking about cause-effect relationship\nType: causal\n\nQuery: \"Compare the GDP of USA and China\"\nReasoning: Comparing two entities\nType: comparative\n\nQuery: \"When did the Renaissance begin?\"\nReasoning: Asking about time/date\nType: temporal\n\nQuery: \"What is photosynthesis?\"\nReasoning: Asking for definition/explanation\nType: definition\n\nQuery: \"Calculate 15% of 240\"\nReasoning: Requiring mathematical calculation\nType: mathematical\n\nAvailable types:\n1. factual - Simple factual questions asking for specific information (who, what, where, name, etc.)\n2. numerical - Questions asking for numbers, counts, quantities, or numerical values\n3. temporal - Questions about time, dates, duration, or chronological relationships\n4. causal - Questions asking why or about cause-and-effect relationships\n5. procedural - Questions asking how to do something or about processes\n6. mathematical - Questions requiring calculations or mathematical operations\n7. comparative - Questions comparing two or more things\n8. definition - Questions asking for definitions or explanations of concepts\n9. general - Complex queries that don't fit into the above categories or require multi-step reasoning\n\nInstructions:\n- Analyze the semantic meaning and intent of the query\n- Consider the complexity and reasoning requirements\n- Return ONLY the type name (one word) without any explanation\n- If uncertain, choose the type that best matches the primary intent\n\nQuery: {query}\nType:",
      "category": "classification",
      "quality_score": 0.9,
      "usage_count": 0,
      "created_at": 1761998299.114379,
      "metadata": {
        "description": "Query type classification prompt template"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "reasoning_step_type_classification",
      "content": "Analyze the following query and context, then return the most appropriate reasoning step type.\n\nExamples:\nQuery: \"What is the capital of France?\"\nContext: \"We need to find factual information\"\nReasoning: This requires analyzing the query to understand what information is needed\nType: query_analysis\n\nQuery: \"How many people live in Tokyo?\"\nContext: \"Population data available\"\nReasoning: Need to gather evidence about Tokyo's population\nType: evidence_gathering\n\nQuery: \"If all birds can fly, and penguins are birds, can penguins fly?\"\nContext: \"Logical contradiction\"\nReasoning: This requires logical deduction to resolve the contradiction\nType: logical_deduction\n\nQuery: \"Why did World War II start?\"\nContext: \"Historical events\"\nReasoning: This requires analyzing cause-effect relationships\nType: causal_reasoning\n\nQuery: \"Calculate the area of a circle with radius 5\"\nContext: \"Mathematical calculation needed\"\nReasoning: This requires mathematical reasoning and calculation\nType: mathematical_reasoning\n\nQuery: \"Compare democracy and autocracy\"\nContext: \"Conceptual comparison\"\nReasoning: This requires comparing concepts using analogies\nType: analogical_reasoning\n\nQuery: \"What patterns exist in these numbers: 2, 4, 8, 16?\"\nContext: \"Number sequence\"\nReasoning: This requires recognizing patterns in the sequence\nType: pattern_recognition\n\nQuery: \"Based on the evidence, what is the final answer?\"\nContext: \"All evidence gathered\"\nReasoning: This requires synthesizing all information into a final answer\nType: answer_synthesis\n\nAvailable types:\n- evidence_gathering - Gathering and collecting relevant evidence\n- query_analysis - Analyzing and understanding the query\n- logical_deduction - Performing logical deduction and inference\n- pattern_recognition - Recognizing patterns and similarities\n- causal_reasoning - Reasoning about cause-and-effect relationships\n- analogical_reasoning - Using analogies and comparisons\n- mathematical_reasoning - Performing mathematical calculations\n- answer_synthesis - Synthesizing the final answer\n\nInstructions:\n- Analyze the query and context to determine the primary reasoning step needed\n- Return ONLY the type name (e.g., \"logical_deduction\") without any explanation\n\nQuery: {query}\nContext: {context}\nType:",
      "category": "classification",
      "quality_score": 0.9,
      "usage_count": 0,
      "created_at": 1761998299.114741,
      "metadata": {
        "description": "Reasoning step type classification prompt template"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "evidence_generation",
      "content": "Generate relevant evidence for the following query. The evidence should be factual, accurate, and directly related to answering the query.\n\nQuery: {query}\n\nRequirements:\n1. Generate concise and relevant evidence\n2. Focus on factual information that helps answer the query\n3. Keep evidence clear and specific\n4. Return only the evidence content, without explanations\n\nEvidence:",
      "category": "evidence",
